Text: —Master Shadow!

Beta trembles with joy. Her faith in her master is
absolute.

Ever since she and the others were young and weak,
he's tirelessly stood before them to fight back the
darkness.

She grew up watching those shoulders. Even against
the Blood Queen, she's sure he'll be fine.

Maybe it's because of how safe he makes her feel, or
maybe it's because of how long it's been since she
last saw him, but she feels almost as though he has
grown even taller.

—The next instant, Elisabeth's eyes open, and the
Blood Queen's magic increases.
The blood comes raining down again.

Shadow fires slime from his cloak, blocking the
falling blood drops.

What powerful magic...! Is he evenly matched with
Lady Elisabeth?!
Shadow...surpasses the Calamity Witch...

Beta feels uneasy in a way she can't quite put into
words.
She watches the battle intently.

For all his skillful defense, none of Shadow's
movements are leading into counterattacks
against the Blood Queen.

Beta knows her master, and she knows that he normally
dodges his opponent's attacks with minimal movement
so he can immediately shift into his counterattack.
...Something is off.
Why is he deliberately engaging her?
He's close enough to strike.
One slash from Master Shadow should be enough to—

Master Shadow's feet are sluggish. His movements
are stiff. He is standing in place and repelling the
feelers manually—it is almost as though he is
protecting something precious.

The next instant, Elisabeth's spear descends above
Beta.
*gasp*
Ack!
Nami!
...It can't be.
Could Master Shadow...
...be shielding us?!
Because we can't move...?!
No matter how heavy the burden,
I can't afford to lose even one.

Ohh...Master Shadow! Your compassionate heart shines
like gold!
I can't afford to lose them...!

Master Shadow...you would go to such lengths for
me...! I won't say another word!
I can't afford...
Hang in there, Master Shadow! You can do it!
...to lose...
You can do it...!
...even one...
Master Shadow!
You can do iiiiiiiit!
...more!
The next instant, Shadow's magic increases.

He leaps forward, instantly closing the distance
between him and Elisabeth.
In Shadow's hand is an ebony blade.
In Elisabeth's hand, a crimson scythe.
—And so, the battle begins anew.
The clash between them leaves a trail in the sky.
That's Master Shadow...! How incredible!
How the hell is that bastard flying?
Maybe...
...he is the real monster...
